1. Use Svelte 5.x compatible syntax and follow best practices as much as possible
2. Framework is SvelteKit
3. Write CSS styles that conform to TailwindCSS 4.x
4. Multilingual support is Paraglide-SvelteKit
5. Write TypeScript 5.x in a way that beginners can understand while following best practices
6. Always declare the type of each variable and function (parameters and return value)
7. Avoid using any
8. Create necessary types
9. Keep functions short and single-purpose (<20 lines)
10. Try to avoid using the Array.reduce() method
11. If asked for suggestions, do not modify the code
